properties.areaDesc: Lower Yampa River Basin; Eastern Uinta Basin
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 24 at 12:17AM MST until January 24 at 10:00AM MST by NWS Grand Junction CO
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility down to quarter mile at times in dense fog.

* WHERE...In Utah, Eastern Uinta Basin. In Colorado, Lower Yampa
River Basin.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM MST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.
This will be most evident along Highway 40 from Roosevelt to
Massadona, including Vernal and Dinosaur, as well as Highway 139
south of Highway 40 including Rangely.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM MST THIS MORNING
